{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry represents the pur operon repressor PurR of low-GC Gram-positive bacteria. This homodimeric repressor contains a large region homologous to phosphoribosyltransferases and is inhibited by 5-phosphoribosyl 1-pyrophosphate [[cite:PUB00013478]].</p>\n\n<p>PurR is a DNA-binding transcriptional repressor that controls the expression of a number of genes involved in the synthesis, metabolism and transport of purines [[cite:PUB00013478], [cite:PUB00155436], [cite:PUB00015789], [cite:PUB00155437]]. In response to a signal of excess adenine, represses the transcription of the pur operon, which encodes enzymes of the purine biosynthetic pathway [[cite:PUB00013478], [cite:PUB00155436]]. it also responds to amino acid starvation via (p)ppGpp, which strongly increases PurR activity and repression of purine nucleotide biosynthesis genes [[cite:PUB00155437]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR029057", "name" "Phosphoribosyltransferase-like", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"ncbifam" {"TIGR01743" "pur operon repressor PurR"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Pur operon repressor", "short" "PurR_Bsub"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 3, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 1171, "taxa" 4086, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 3710, "sets" 0, "proteins" 3710, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 2922}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR010078", :literature {"PUB00013478" {"URL" nil, "issue" "16", "authors" ["Weng M" "Nagy PL" "Zalkin H."], "ISO_journal" "Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A.", "DOI_URL" "http://ukpmc.ac.uk/picrender.cgi?tool=EBI&pubmedid=7638212&action=stream&blobtype=pdf", "medline_journal" "Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A", "title" "Identification of the Bacillus subtilis pur operon repres